Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water from your #kettle{} into a large #saucepan{} on high
heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Add the @macaroni{180%g} to the water and bring
back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to
stop it sticking together. Set aside.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the garlic for ~{30%secs}.

Add the @water for the sauce{50%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and cooked
pasta to the pan. Bring to the boil, stirring constantly, then remove from
the heat.

Vigorously stir the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @wholegrain mustard{17%g} and both
the grated Cheddar and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} into the
macaroni.

Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's a
little too thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the mac & cheese between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @chilli flakes{1%pinch}.

Serve the @pea shoots{40%g} alongside and drizzle over the
@balsamic glaze{12%ml} and a little @olive oil{}.

Enjoy!

> Add less chilli flakes if you'd prefer things milder.